			<h3 ><a href="#p1685298">Re: Car Insurance Advice</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1685298&amp;sid=dbd612b095921ececc91042871a29805#p1685298"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=470&amp;sid=dbd612b095921ececc91042871a29805">jsl11</a></strong> &raquo; Fri May 03, 2013 3:20 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">What is the premium for the compehensive coverage alone?  Your premium statement should itemize the coverages.  That will tell you what you would save by dropping the coverage.  I have a vehicle similar to yours.  I keep the comprehensive coverage because it costs very little.  You can probably also get some lower costs by paying your premium annually or semiannually instead of monthly.<br />Jeff</div>

			

		</div>

		
