			<h3 ><a href="#p1685307">Re: Car Insurance Advice</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1685307&amp;sid=dbd612b095921ececc91042871a29805#p1685307"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1901&amp;sid=dbd612b095921ececc91042871a29805">Quasimodo</a></strong> &raquo; Fri May 03, 2013 3:30 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">A rule of thumb I've seen is that if your total comprehensive and collision premium exceeds 10 percent of the vehicle's market value, it's probably not worth your while to continue to carry these coverages.<br /><br />Good luck whatever you decide!<br /><br />John</div>

			<div id="sig1685307" class="signature">Many wealthy people are little more than janitors of their possessions. <br /><br />Frank Lloyd Wright, architect (1867-1959)</div>

